        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 8 at 11:44PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1144 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southwest of Miami, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Miami and Codman.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
